This paper focuses on reinforcement learning and generalisation to unseen tasks, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of function approximators and policy improvement methods also suggests a focus on machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with navigation in a three-dimensional environment, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of successor features also suggests a focus on control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques is also likely given the focus on RL and generalisation.
